• Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. PRETORIA - Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe will meet with President Jacob Zuma in Pretoria to strengthen ties between the two neighbours.
	
	Mugabe is not accompanied by the First Lady Grace Mugabe, In August, she left under a cloud after she was granted diplomatic immunity. READ: SA, Zim Ministers vow to boost trade, create jobs She allegedly assaulted a young South African woman with an extension cord. The bilateral meeting comes as Zimbabwe faces serious shortages, with people resorting to panic buying. The countries have over 40 agreements in place to boost trade and co-operation in areas including mining, agriculture, and finance. eNCA